      <strong>Operating in Phoenix:</strong> Yes.<br />
      <strong>Typical offer:</strong> Mid-range 65-78% ARV.<br />
      <strong>Typical close:</strong> 14-30 days.<br />
      <strong>Best for:</strong> Standard cash-sale process with a slightly larger operation than the smallest independent buyers. Some seller preference for working with a company versus an individual investor.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Pros:</strong> Larger operational backbone than typical local investors. Multi-state presence provides some operational redundancy.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Cons:</strong> Larger size translates to slightly higher overhead, which sometimes shows up in marginally lower offers. Decision-making process can involve multiple internal approvals, which slows responsiveness on time-sensitive deals.
